<figureCitation box="[681,774,406,432]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1924,1950]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,303,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-11@7.[189,1398,303,1844]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 1. Amblypsilopus ankarana sp. nov. Holotype, ♂ (AMGS). A. Habitus. B. Head. C. Antenna. D. Fore femur and tibia. E. Fore tarsus. F. Wing. G. Hypopygium, left lateral view, reflected light. H. Surstylus, ventrolateral view, transmitted light." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4983306" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4983306/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
